  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Enumeration District - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_enumeration_district">Enumeration District</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_geographic_area">GEOGRAPHIC AREA</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_enumeration_district">Enumeration District</xref>
 (
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_enumeration_district">ED</xref>
), also known as a 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_enumeration_district">Census Enumeration District</xref>
, is used across the United Kingdom for the purposes of census data collection.  </p>
  <p>
For further information on 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_enumeration_district">Enumeration Districts</xref>
, see the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_office_for_national_statistics">Office for National Statistics</xref>
 website at: 
    <xref href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/census/2001censusandearlier/glossary/ag"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Glossary</xref>
.  </p>

